2pt">Chief Constable. This sets the overall, high level strategy within which the draft budget is prepared.    </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="21" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Force prepares the initial draft revenue budget, medium term financial plan and draft 3-4 year capital programme</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> prior to presentation to me</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="22" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Regular meetings are held at officer level to ensure that the budgeting process is reliable, robust, accurate and is in accordance with my overall aims and objectives</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> as set out in my Police and Crime Plan.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  I also discuss key budget issues </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">as necessary and appropriate </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">with the Chief Constable at our regular bi-weekly </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">liaison </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">meetings, </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="23" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2% increase in council tax </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">precept increase for 2013/14 was in accordance with my election manifesto commitment</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to protect local policing in the Thames Valley.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="24" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The draft budget for 2014/15 reflects my </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">intention</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to increase the police precept by 2%</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, again to protect the impact of budget cuts on local operational policing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="25" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">My staff work very closely with the Force to identify budget reductions and to understand the impact these will have on local policing and local communities.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-indent:6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="26" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I have already </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">provided</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> draft budget papers to the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">P</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">olice and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">C</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">rime </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">P</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">anel</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and the Force Director of Finance and my own CFO attended a recent</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> meeting of the Panel’s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> budget task and finish group to take members through the detailed budget papers and answer their queries and concerns.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  This process helps inform the Panel on the service priorities and financial plans that the proposed council tax increase will underpin.</span></li></ol></td></tr><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:19.6pt"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:442.5pt"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:19.6pt"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">F</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:442.5pt"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The effectiveness of commissioners in promoting local policing priorities</span></p></td></tr><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:19.6pt"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4p